column14:
Informed Consent Form



Professor Debra Lieberman is conducting an experiment to learn more about the actions that cause people to feel gratitude.



Description of Study



You will be asked to complete a series of questions about how much gratitude you think you would feel in response to various actions done by others.



Confidentiality



All of your answers will be kept confidential and will only be seen by the research team for data analysis, or by auditing or compliance officials who are bound to the same confidentiality requirements.



Risks and Inconveniences



There is no known risk involved in participating in the study. The study will take about 15 minutes to complete. Participation is voluntary, and if you agree to be in this study, but later change your mind, you may drop out at any time. There are no penalties or consequences of any kind if you decide you do not want to participate.



Questions



If you have any questions about this study, please contact Dr. Debra Lieberman by email at debra@miami.edu.  If you have any questions about your rights as a research participant, contact the University of Miami Human Subjects Research Office at 305-243-3195.



“By agreeing to participate in this research (and by pressing the I WISH TO PARTICIPATE button at the bottom of this page) you acknowledge that you have read and understand this consent form, that you understand the risks and potential benefits associated with your participation, and that you wish to participate in the research as described.”
